    <div xml:id="PaLTM3.5.1">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>aṭṭukkuvicōṟṟupparuppatamum</l>
<l>tayirvāviyumneyyaḷaṟumaṭaṅkap</l>
<l>poṭṭattuṟṟi mārippakaipuṇartta</l>
<l>porumākaṭalvaṇṇaṉpoṟuttamalai</l>
<l>vaṭṭattaṭaṅkaṇmaṭamāṉkaṉṟiṉai</l>
<l>valaivāyppaṟṟikkoṇṭu kuṟamakaḷir</l>
<l>koṭṭaittalaippālkoṭuttuvaḷarkkum</l>
<l>kōvarttaṉameṉṉumkoṟṟakkuṭaiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The mountain that the one with a complexion [like] the great, churning sea -</l>
<l rend="indent">who brought about the enmity of the rain clouds after [he] swiftly and thoroughly ate
 the heaping mountain of cooked rice, river of curd, and bog of ghee -
</l>
<l>bore, called Govardhana,</l> 
<l rend="indent">where little girls catch simple, round, wide eyed fawn in nets and take [them] 
to give [them] milk on the end of a cloth knot [to suckle] and raise [them],</l>
<l>is [his] victory umbrella.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
